This paper discusses a decentralized algorithm for traffic control, which involves coordination between multiple agents. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Multiagent Systems (cs.MA) sub-category. Additionally, the algorithm involves communication between agents, which could fall under the Networked Systems (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of real-time data to construct schedules, which could be related to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The algorithm is designed to optimize traffic flow, which could be related to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the scalability of the algorithm, which could be related to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category.
